Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @Cremini Mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}.

Place @Flatbreads{2} on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Toast on top rack until lightly golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from oven. (For 4 servings, divide flatbreads between two sheets; toast on top and middle racks.)

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{4%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Lower heat and add a splash of water if mushrooms begin to brown too quickly.

Add onion and another drizzle of oil; season with @Italian Seasoning{1%tablespoon} and a big pinch of @Salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring, until veggies are browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and @Pepper{} if desired. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, in a small #pot{}, heat @Cream Sauce Base{4%ounce} over medium-high heat until gently bubbling, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium; tear @Gouda Cheese{2%slice} into pieces and add to pot. Whisk until melted and combined.

Remove pot from heat; stir in half the @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings) until thoroughly combined.

Spread gouda sauce over flatbreads. Top with mushroom mixture and @Parmesan Cheese{3%tablespoon}. Return flatbreads to top rack until cheese melts and edges are golden brown, ~{6-10%minutes}. (For 4 servings, return sheets to top and middle racks; swap positions halfway through baking.)

Cut flatbreads into pieces and divide between plates. Serve.